#. <section class="sutta" id="an11.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an11.7:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 11"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 11"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an11.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Nissayavagga"
msgstr "1. Dependence"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an11.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Saññāsutta"
msgstr "7. Percipient"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an11.7:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an11.7:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Siyā nu kho, bhante, bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā neva "
"pathaviyaṃ pathavisaññī assa, na āpasmiṃ āposaññī assa, na tejasmiṃ "
"tejosaññī assa, na vāyasmiṃ vāyosaññī assa, na ākāsānañcāyatane "
"ākāsānañcāyatanasaññī assa, na viññāṇañcāyatane viññāṇañcāyatanasaññī assa, "
"na ākiñcaññāyatane ākiñcaññāyatanasaññī assa, na nevasaññānāsaññāyatane "
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasaññī assa, na idhaloke idhalokasaññī assa, na "
"paraloke paralokasaññī assa, yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ "
"pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā, tatrāpi na saññī assa; saññī ca pana "
"assā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Could it be, sir, that a mendicant might gain a state of immersion like "
"this? They wouldn’t perceive earth in earth, water in water, fire in fire, "
"or air in air. And they wouldn’t perceive the dimension of infinite space in "
"the dimension of infinite space, the dimension of infinite consciousness in "
"the dimension of infinite consciousness, the dimension of nothingness in the "
"dimension of nothingness, or the dimension of neither perception nor non-"
"perception in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. They "
"wouldn’t perceive this world in this world, or the other world in the other "
"world. And they wouldn’t perceive what is seen, heard, thought, cognized, "
"attained, sought, or explored by the mind. And yet they would still "
"perceive.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.319"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an11.7:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Siyā, ānanda, bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā neva pathaviyaṃ "
"pathavisaññī assa, na āpasmiṃ āposaññī assa, na tejasmiṃ tejosaññī assa, na "
"vāyasmiṃ vāyosaññī assa, na ākāsānañcāyatane ākāsānañcāyatanasaññī assa, na "
"viññāṇañcāyatane viññāṇañcāyatanasaññī assa, na ākiñcaññāyatane "
"ākiñcaññāyatanasaññī assa, na nevasaññānāsaññāyatane "
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasaññī assa, na idhaloke idhalokasaññī assa, na "
"paraloke paralokasaññī assa, yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ "
"pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā, tatrāpi na saññī assa; saññī ca pana "
"assā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“It could be, Ānanda, that a mendicant might gain a state of immersion like "
"this. They wouldn’t perceive earth in earth, water in water, fire in fire, "
"or air in air. And they wouldn’t perceive the dimension of infinite space in "
"the dimension of infinite space, the dimension of infinite consciousness in "
"the dimension of infinite consciousness, the dimension of nothingness in the "
"dimension of nothingness, or the dimension of neither perception nor non-"
"perception in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. They "
"wouldn’t perceive this world in this world, or the other world in the other "
"world. And they wouldn’t perceive what is seen, heard, thought, cognized, "
"attained, sought, or explored by the mind. And yet they would still "
"perceive.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an11.7:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bhante, siyā bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā "
"neva pathaviyaṃ pathavisaññī assa, na āpasmiṃ āposaññī assa, na tejasmiṃ "
"tejosaññī assa, na vāyasmiṃ vāyosaññī assa, na ākāsānañcāyatane "
"ākāsānañcāyatanasaññī assa, na viññāṇañcāyatane viññāṇañcāyatanasaññī assa, "
"na ākiñcaññāyatane ākiñcaññāyatanasaññī assa, na nevasaññānāsaññāyatane "
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasaññī assa, na idhaloke idhalokasaññī assa, na "
"paraloke paralokasaññī assa, yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ "
"pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā, tatrāpi na saññī assa, saññī ca pana "
"assā”ti."
msgstr "“But how could this be, sir?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an11.7:5.1"
msgid "“Idhānanda, bhikkhu evaṃsaññī hoti:"
msgstr "“Ānanda, it’s when a mendicant perceives:"

msgctxt "an11.7:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ, yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho "
"sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is peaceful; this is sublime—that is, the stilling of all activities, "
"the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading away, "
"cessation, extinguishment.’"

msgctxt "an11.7:5.3"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, ānanda, siyā bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā neva "
"pathaviyaṃ pathavisaññī assa, na āpasmiṃ āposaññī assa, na tejasmiṃ "
"tejosaññī assa, na vāyasmiṃ vāyosaññī assa, na ākāsānañcāyatane "
"ākāsānañcāyatanasaññī assa, na viññāṇañcāyatane viññāṇañcāyatanasaññī assa, "
"na ākiñcaññāyatane ākiñcaññāyatanasaññī assa, na nevasaññānāsaññāyatane "
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasaññī assa, na idhaloke idhalokasaññī assa, na "
"paraloke paralokasaññī assa, yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ "
"pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā, tatrāpi na saññī assa, saññī ca pana "
"assā”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant might gain a state of immersion like this. They "
"wouldn’t perceive earth in earth, water in water, fire in fire, or air in "
"air. And they wouldn’t perceive the dimension of infinite space in the "
"dimension of infinite space, the dimension of infinite consciousness in the "
"dimension of infinite consciousness, the dimension of nothingness in the "
"dimension of nothingness, or the dimension of neither perception nor non-"
"perception in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. They "
"wouldn’t perceive this world in this world, or the other world in the other "
"world. And they wouldn’t perceive what is seen, heard, thought, cognized, "
"attained, sought, or explored by the mind. And yet they would still "
"perceive.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.320"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an11.7:6.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā "
"uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yenāyasmā sāriputto "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"And then Ānanda approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. He got up "
"from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on "
"his right. Then he went up to Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings "
"with him."

msgctxt "an11.7:6.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho āyasmā ānando āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to Sāriputta:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an11.7:7.1"
msgid ""
"“Siyā nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā "
"neva pathaviyaṃ pathavisaññī assa … pe … yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ "
"viññātaṃ pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā, tatrāpi na saññī assa, "
"saññī pana assā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Could it be, reverend Sāriputta, that a mendicant might gain a state of "
"immersion like this? They wouldn’t perceive earth in earth … And they wouldn’"
"t perceive what is seen, heard, thought, cognized, attained, sought, or "
"explored by the mind. And yet they would still perceive.”"

msgctxt "an11.7:7.2"
msgid ""
"“Siyā, āvuso ānanda, bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā neva "
"pathaviyaṃ pathavisaññī assa … pe … yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ "
"pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā, tatrāpi na saññī assa, saññī ca pana "
"assā”ti."
msgstr "“It could be, Reverend Ānanda.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an11.7:8.1"
msgid ""
"“Yathā kathaṃ panāvuso sāriputta, siyā bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho "
"yathā neva pathaviyaṃ pathavisaññī assa … pe … yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ "
"viññātaṃ pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā, tatrāpi na saññī assa, "
"saññī ca pana assā”ti?"
msgstr "“But how could this be?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an11.7:9.1"
msgid "“Idha, āvuso ānanda, bhikkhu evaṃsaññī hoti:"
msgstr "“Ānanda, it’s when a mendicant perceives:"

msgctxt "an11.7:9.2"
msgid ""
"‘etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ, yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho "
"sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is peaceful; this is sublime—that is, the stilling of all activities, "
"the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading away, "
"cessation, extinguishment.’"

msgctxt "an11.7:9.3"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, āvuso ānanda, siyā bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā neva "
"pathaviyaṃ pathavisaññī assa … pe … yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ "
"pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā, tatrāpi na saññī assa, saññī ca pana "
"assā”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant might gain a state of immersion like this. They "
"wouldn’t perceive earth in earth … And they wouldn’t perceive what is seen, "
"heard, thought, cognized, attained, sought, or explored by the mind. And yet "
"they would still perceive.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.321"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an11.7:10.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "an11.7:10.2"
msgid ""
"Yatra hi nāma satthu ceva sāvakassa ca atthena attho byañjanena byañjanaṃ "
"saṃsandissati samessati na viggayhissati, yadidaṃ aggapadasmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"How the meaning and the phrasing of the teacher and the disciple fit "
"together and agree without conflict when it comes to the chief matter!"

msgctxt "an11.7:10.3"
msgid "Idānāhaṃ, āvuso, bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ apucchiṃ."
msgstr "Just now I went to the Buddha and asked him about this matter."

msgctxt "an11.7:10.4"
msgid ""
"Bhagavāpi me etehi akkharehi etehi padehi etehi byañjanehi etamatthaṃ "
"byākāsi, seyyathāpi āyasmā sāriputto."
msgstr ""
"And the Buddha explained it to me in this manner, with these words and "
"phrases, just like Venerable Sāriputta."

msgctxt "an11.7:10.5"
msgid "Acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso."
msgstr "It’s incredible, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "an11.7:10.6"
msgid ""
"Yatra hi nāma satthu ceva sāvakassa ca atthena attho byañjanena byañjanaṃ "
"saṃsandissati samessati na viggayhissati, yadidaṃ aggapadasmin”ti."
msgstr ""
"How the meaning and the phrasing of the teacher and the disciple fit "
"together and agree without conflict when it comes to the chief matter!”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an11.7:10.7"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
